SIMPLE: preserver
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preserver
<hw>Pre*serv"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who, or that which, preserves, saves, or defends, from destruction,
injury, or decay; esp., one who saves the life or character of
another.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who makes preserves of fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Game preserver</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Game</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preshow</ent>⟦br⟧
